.TH "evm_inode_post_setattr" 9 "evm_inode_post_setattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
evm_inode_post_setattr \- update 'security.evm' after modifying metadata
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" evm_inode_post_setattr
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "int ia_valid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
pointer to the affected dentry
.IP "ia_valid" 12
for the UID and GID status
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For now, update the HMAC stored in 'security.evm' to reflect UID/GID
changes.

This function is called from \fBnotify_change\fP, which expects the caller
to lock the inode's i_mutex.
